### Active users for PIN login selection (`hasPin` shows whether PIN login is available)
GET http://localhost:3100/api/auth/active-users

### Password login (existing path remains active and pairs with the `/login` password fallback UI)
POST http://localhost:3100/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "replace-with-existing-user-email",
  "password": "replace-with-existing-user-password"
}

### PIN status for current user
GET http://localhost:3100/api/auth/pin-status

### Set PIN for current user
POST http://localhost:3100/api/auth/pin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pin": "1234"
}

### Change PIN for current user
PATCH http://localhost:3100/api/auth/pin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPin": "1234",
  "nextPin": "5678"
}

### PIN login
POST http://localhost:3100/api/auth/pin-login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "replace-with-user-id",
  "pin": "5678"
}

### Manager/admin reset another user's PIN
POST http://localhost:3100/api/admin/users/replace-with-user-id/reset-pin

### Manager/admin set another user's PIN directly
POST http://localhost:3100/api/admin/users/replace-with-user-id/set-pin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pin": "2468"
}
